function minDifference(nums) {
    let n = nums.length;
    if (n <= 4) return 0;
    nums.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let res = Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER;
    for (let i = 0; i <= 3; ++i)
        res = Math.min(res, nums[n - 4 + i] - nums[i]);
    return res;
}
```

    1. First, check if the length of the input array is less than or equal to 4. If it is, return 0 since there's no need to perform any operation on this input.
2. Sort the input array in ascending order.
3. Initialize the result (minimum difference) as the maximum value possible.
4. Loop through the array from the 0-th element to the 3-rd element (inclusive). For each iteration, find the difference between the (n - 4 + i)-th element and the i-th element in the sorted array, where n is the length of the input array. Update the result as the minimum of the current and previous minimum differences.
5. After the loop, return the resulting minimum difference.

